The paper investigates fundamental questions related to locating and defining features in convolutional neural networks (CNN), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new regularization method for improving the accuracy of CNNs, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses theoretical investigations related to the locality principle, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on multiple datasets, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
